<span id="freeTextContainer5829860407564260568">&quot;What the hell is he doing evaluating her mouth?&quot; Yeah, bro, I&apos;m wondering that too. This is like a parody the male-narrated, female body obsessed book. Sabbath&apos;s theater without the tongue in cheek. <br/>A libertarian, Reddit-user male fantasy where the bad-ass CIA agent is constantly surrounded by women and mansplaining to them his views on religion, climate change, politics, sex, alcohol, birth control, art, literature, beauty.... etc., ad nauseam. Sone of the floweriest language I&apos;ve ever read, f</span>
  <span id="freeText5829860407564260568" style="display:none">"What the hell is he doing evaluating her mouth?" Yeah, bro, I'm wondering that too. This is like a parody the male-narrated, female body obsessed book. Sabbath's theater without the tongue in cheek. <br />A libertarian, Reddit-user male fantasy where the bad-ass CIA agent is constantly surrounded by women and mansplaining to them his views on religion, climate change, politics, sex, alcohol, birth control, art, literature, beauty.... etc., ad nauseam. Sone of the floweriest language I've ever read, for better or for worse. No-holds-barred shove in your face of how smart the author is. But an intriguing story and, again, the writing is amazing. Poor mans David Foster Wallace </span>
